WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:00.570 align:middle line:90%


00:00:00.570 --> 00:00:04.940 align:middle line:84%
>>Ron Davis was born as an
autistic and dyslexic in a time

00:00:04.940 --> 00:00:07.840 align:middle line:84%
when there was little compassion
for those who were different.

00:00:07.840 --> 00:00:09.510 align:middle line:84%
This heart rending
story takes us

00:00:09.510 --> 00:00:12.510 align:middle line:84%
into the mind of someone who was
unable to communicate and tell

00:00:12.510 --> 00:00:14.130 align:middle line:90%
the age of 17.

00:00:14.130 --> 00:00:16.600 align:middle line:90%
By 19 he was teaching calculus.

00:00:16.600 --> 00:00:19.670 align:middle line:84%
At 36 he was a millionaire,
but still ashamed

00:00:19.670 --> 00:00:20.860 align:middle line:90%
that he couldn't read.

00:00:20.860 --> 00:00:24.140 align:middle line:84%
That's when the lights went on
and he discovered that dyslexia

00:00:24.140 --> 00:00:27.160 align:middle line:84%
is a gift that can be
turned off and on that will.

00:00:27.160 --> 00:00:35.850 align:middle line:90%


00:00:35.850 --> 00:00:39.180 align:middle line:84%
>>So Ron, let's start
at the beginning.

00:00:39.180 --> 00:00:41.570 align:middle line:84%
Your story is not
only unique, it's

00:00:41.570 --> 00:00:43.500 align:middle line:90%
very heart rending as well.

00:00:43.500 --> 00:00:45.930 align:middle line:84%
You had a pretty bumpy
start to this life.

00:00:45.930 --> 00:00:51.110 align:middle line:84%
Can you tell us how
you journey began.

00:00:51.110 --> 00:00:55.130 align:middle line:84%
>>As an infant, my mother was
told I was a Kanners baby.

00:00:55.130 --> 00:00:57.480 align:middle line:84%
Doctor Leo Kanner
coined the word "autism"

00:00:57.480 --> 00:00:58.990 align:middle line:90%
in the United States.

00:00:58.990 --> 00:01:03.320 align:middle line:84%
But I was actually born the
year before it was published.

00:01:03.320 --> 00:01:06.090 align:middle line:84%
So I was never actually
called artistic,

00:01:06.090 --> 00:01:08.730 align:middle line:84%
I was only called
a Kanners baby.

00:01:08.730 --> 00:01:13.020 align:middle line:84%
And I don't know what my mother
was told about Kanners babies.

00:01:13.020 --> 00:01:16.250 align:middle line:84%
I don't know if she was
told of the probability

00:01:16.250 --> 00:01:18.490 align:middle line:84%
that I would have
grandma epilepsy.

00:01:18.490 --> 00:01:21.900 align:middle line:84%
Or the possibility that I would
never develop enough language

00:01:21.900 --> 00:01:23.720 align:middle line:90%
skills to even talk to her.

00:01:23.720 --> 00:01:26.895 align:middle line:84%
Or that I would never allow
her to hold me, or cuddle me,

00:01:26.895 --> 00:01:29.160 align:middle line:90%
or treat me like a normal child.

00:01:29.160 --> 00:01:33.140 align:middle line:84%
And that I might only have the
intelligence of the chimpanzee.

00:01:33.140 --> 00:01:36.165 align:middle line:84%
My mother was very good hearing
only what you wanted to hear.

00:01:36.165 --> 00:01:40.570 align:middle line:84%
And what my mother heard
was, I was going to be slow.

00:01:40.570 --> 00:01:42.030 align:middle line:84%
At the end of the
Second World War,

00:01:42.030 --> 00:01:44.380 align:middle line:84%
when my father came
home from the war,

00:01:44.380 --> 00:01:46.540 align:middle line:84%
he was very surprised
to find that he

00:01:46.540 --> 00:01:49.950 align:middle line:84%
had a three year old,
mentally deficient child.

00:01:49.950 --> 00:01:52.865 align:middle line:84%
That surprise very
quickly turned into anger,

00:01:52.865 --> 00:01:55.416 align:middle line:90%
and then hatred.

00:01:55.416 --> 00:02:01.660 align:middle line:84%
And when the time came for
me to start into school,

00:02:01.660 --> 00:02:03.310 align:middle line:84%
the school put
pressure on my parents

00:02:03.310 --> 00:02:06.350 align:middle line:84%
to have me put into
an institution.

00:02:06.350 --> 00:02:09.370 align:middle line:84%
My mother was in
denial, and my father

00:02:09.370 --> 00:02:12.410 align:middle line:84%
would have been very
happy to have me go away.

00:02:12.410 --> 00:02:14.512 align:middle line:84%
And essentially, my
mom told the school,

00:02:14.512 --> 00:02:16.470 align:middle line:84%
he's going to be slow
but you have to take him.

00:02:16.470 --> 00:02:19.450 align:middle line:90%


00:02:19.450 --> 00:02:21.140 align:middle line:84%
The school really
didn't know what

00:02:21.140 --> 00:02:23.070 align:middle line:90%
to do with someone like me.

00:02:23.070 --> 00:02:26.160 align:middle line:84%
So I wound up sitting in
the corner of the room

00:02:26.160 --> 00:02:28.380 align:middle line:90%
with a handkerchief on my head.

00:02:28.380 --> 00:02:30.540 align:middle line:84%
And I'm often asked,
why the handkerchief?

00:02:30.540 --> 00:02:32.890 align:middle line:84%
And tell you the
truth, I don't know.

00:02:32.890 --> 00:02:34.730 align:middle line:84%
I was a person
wearing it, I wasn't

00:02:34.730 --> 00:02:35.985 align:middle line:90%
the person that put it there.

00:02:35.985 --> 00:02:37.860 align:middle line:84%
>>Oh, you were labeled
with the handkerchief.

00:02:37.860 --> 00:02:39.068 align:middle line:90%
You didn't do it to yourself?

00:02:39.068 --> 00:02:40.220 align:middle line:90%
>>No, no, no, no.

00:02:40.220 --> 00:02:43.650 align:middle line:84%
In fact, my back to the room
and my nose was in the corner.

00:02:43.650 --> 00:02:46.430 align:middle line:84%
And if that handkerchief
ever fell off, boy, I

00:02:46.430 --> 00:02:49.030 align:middle line:84%
would get a good hard whack,
they'd put it back on,

00:02:49.030 --> 00:02:51.880 align:middle line:84%
and stick my nose
tight into the corner.

00:02:51.880 --> 00:02:54.600 align:middle line:84%
>>May I ask you a
question at this point,

00:02:54.600 --> 00:02:57.010 align:middle line:84%
because I want to hear where
this story goes from here.

00:02:57.010 --> 00:02:57.740 align:middle line:90%
>>Sure.

00:02:57.740 --> 00:03:00.185 align:middle line:84%
>>But as you were sitting
there with your nose

00:03:00.185 --> 00:03:01.935 align:middle line:84%
pointed into the corner
and a handkerchief

00:03:01.935 --> 00:03:05.980 align:middle line:84%
on you head, what was
going on in your world?

00:03:05.980 --> 00:03:11.800 align:middle line:84%
>>Well, for most of the time
I was oblivious to everything.

00:03:11.800 --> 00:03:16.600 align:middle line:84%
Developmentally, I didn't
begin to actually develop

00:03:16.600 --> 00:03:19.260 align:middle line:84%
at all until around
the age of nine.

00:03:19.260 --> 00:03:22.970 align:middle line:84%
And I think that, emotionally
and psychologically,

00:03:22.970 --> 00:03:25.810 align:middle line:84%
I did between the
ages of nine and 12,

00:03:25.810 --> 00:03:29.900 align:middle line:84%
what a normal child does between
birth and the age of two.

00:03:29.900 --> 00:03:32.740 align:middle line:84%
And I did between
the ages of 12 and 15

00:03:32.740 --> 00:03:36.400 align:middle line:84%
what a normal child does between
the ages of two and four.

00:03:36.400 --> 00:03:40.740 align:middle line:84%
So for the first
six years or so I

00:03:40.740 --> 00:03:42.560 align:middle line:84%
was totally oblivious
to everything

00:03:42.560 --> 00:03:44.080 align:middle line:90%
that was going on around me.

00:03:44.080 --> 00:03:48.790 align:middle line:84%
But as I began to develop out
of the autism, I became aware.

00:03:48.790 --> 00:03:50.660 align:middle line:84%
I became aware that
I was different

00:03:50.660 --> 00:03:53.370 align:middle line:84%
and that I was being
treated differently.

00:03:53.370 --> 00:03:56.660 align:middle line:84%
And literally, by the
time I was 12 years old,

00:03:56.660 --> 00:03:59.020 align:middle line:84%
there wasn't a sin or a crime
I wouldn't have committed

00:03:59.020 --> 00:04:02.120 align:middle line:84%
with a great big grin on my face
if it would have gotten me out

00:04:02.120 --> 00:04:03.780 align:middle line:90%
of the corner of the room.

00:04:03.780 --> 00:04:06.400 align:middle line:84%
But what they wanted
me to do I couldn't do.

00:04:06.400 --> 00:04:08.070 align:middle line:90%
I couldn't learn.

00:04:08.070 --> 00:04:13.012 align:middle line:84%
When I was 12 years old I
didn't even know my own name.

00:04:13.012 --> 00:04:14.470 align:middle line:84%
Now, I knew where
to go to go home,

00:04:14.470 --> 00:04:16.761 align:middle line:84%
but I didn't know the name
of the street or the number.

00:04:16.761 --> 00:04:18.709 align:middle line:84%
And it wouldn't
have been any value

00:04:18.709 --> 00:04:20.870 align:middle line:84%
to know those things
anyway, because when

00:04:20.870 --> 00:04:25.170 align:middle line:84%
I was 12 I still hadn't
learn how to talk.

00:04:25.170 --> 00:04:27.260 align:middle line:90%
So I don't know what happened.

00:04:27.260 --> 00:04:29.250 align:middle line:84%
At the beginning of
every school year

00:04:29.250 --> 00:04:30.880 align:middle line:84%
there was pressure
put on my parents

00:04:30.880 --> 00:04:34.124 align:middle line:84%
to have me taken away
or labeled something.

00:04:34.124 --> 00:04:35.540 align:middle line:84%
And at the beginning
of every year

00:04:35.540 --> 00:04:37.580 align:middle line:84%
I'm sure my mother
told them, he's slow,

00:04:37.580 --> 00:04:39.250 align:middle line:90%
but you have to keep him.

00:04:39.250 --> 00:04:42.260 align:middle line:84%
So the year I was 12
something happened.

00:04:42.260 --> 00:04:45.610 align:middle line:84%
I don't know if the laws
changed and the school could

00:04:45.610 --> 00:04:48.420 align:middle line:84%
act without my mother,
or if my mother finally

00:04:48.420 --> 00:04:50.720 align:middle line:90%
gave in to their pressure.

00:04:50.720 --> 00:04:54.890 align:middle line:84%
But the year I was 12, the words
uneducatable mental retardation

00:04:54.890 --> 00:04:57.010 align:middle line:90%
were put into my school records.

00:04:57.010 --> 00:05:00.090 align:middle line:84%
And that labeling, for me,
was both something wonderful

00:05:00.090 --> 00:05:02.090 align:middle line:90%
and something that was terrible.

00:05:02.090 --> 00:05:04.000 align:middle line:84%
It was wonderful because
with that labeling,

00:05:04.000 --> 00:05:06.790 align:middle line:84%
I no longer had to sit in
the corner of the room.

00:05:06.790 --> 00:05:08.470 align:middle line:90%
In fact, I even changed schools.

00:05:08.470 --> 00:05:10.720 align:middle line:84%
But I wasn't put
into a school that

00:05:10.720 --> 00:05:15.800 align:middle line:84%
was for mentally retarded
children, that labeling was

00:05:15.800 --> 00:05:18.270 align:middle line:84%
both a blessing
and a curse for me.

00:05:18.270 --> 00:05:20.430 align:middle line:84%
It was a blessing
because I no longer had

00:05:20.430 --> 00:05:22.990 align:middle line:84%
to sit in the
corner of the room.

00:05:22.990 --> 00:05:24.800 align:middle line:84%
I also got to change
schools, but I

00:05:24.800 --> 00:05:27.830 align:middle line:84%
wasn't put into a school for
mentally retarded children,

00:05:27.830 --> 00:05:30.620 align:middle line:84%
I was just put it into a school
where the other children didn't

00:05:30.620 --> 00:05:34.040 align:middle line:90%
know about me or who I was.

00:05:34.040 --> 00:05:36.550 align:middle line:84%
And I like magic,
I start stopped

00:05:36.550 --> 00:05:38.300 align:middle line:84%
wetting my pants
every day in school.

00:05:38.300 --> 00:05:42.070 align:middle line:84%
And the other children
stopped teasing me.

00:05:42.070 --> 00:05:46.840 align:middle line:84%
But I still was referred to
by the teachers as the MR kid,

00:05:46.840 --> 00:05:48.770 align:middle line:90%
or an idiot, or an imbecile.

00:05:48.770 --> 00:05:53.350 align:middle line:84%
And that word imbecile is one
that I particularly don't like.

00:05:53.350 --> 00:05:57.080 align:middle line:84%
Only name than I ever had a
home from my father was dummy.

00:05:57.080 --> 00:05:59.710 align:middle line:84%
And I guess that was
the best of all of them,

00:05:59.710 --> 00:06:03.370 align:middle line:84%
because dummy
means the inability

00:06:03.370 --> 00:06:06.420 align:middle line:90%
to speak and not very bright.

00:06:06.420 --> 00:06:11.120 align:middle line:84%
And at that time, I think I fit
into both of those categories.

00:06:11.120 --> 00:06:15.250 align:middle line:84%
But later, that
labeling was a curse.

00:06:15.250 --> 00:06:17.820 align:middle line:84%
Later in my life,
if my colleagues

00:06:17.820 --> 00:06:22.300 align:middle line:84%
would have discovered that
those words were attached to me,

00:06:22.300 --> 00:06:23.760 align:middle line:90%
I would've simply died of shame.

00:06:23.760 --> 00:06:27.390 align:middle line:90%


00:06:27.390 --> 00:06:29.740 align:middle line:84%
Can you imagine
the embarrassment

00:06:29.740 --> 00:06:32.850 align:middle line:90%
that a person would experience?

00:06:32.850 --> 00:06:36.570 align:middle line:84%
I'm faking it, pretending
to be a real human being.

00:06:36.570 --> 00:06:39.230 align:middle line:84%
And then other people
find out that actually I

00:06:39.230 --> 00:06:40.720 align:middle line:90%
was mentally retarded.

00:06:40.720 --> 00:06:44.640 align:middle line:84%
And actually, it goes a
little deeper than that.

00:06:44.640 --> 00:06:49.760 align:middle line:84%
When I was 12 my
mom was told that I

00:06:49.760 --> 00:06:52.260 align:middle line:84%
had the intelligence
of the chimpanzee.

00:06:52.260 --> 00:06:54.630 align:middle line:84%
My mother was told
that I had an IQ of 40,

00:06:54.630 --> 00:06:57.169 align:middle line:84%
and a chimpanzee
has an IQ of 40.

00:06:57.169 --> 00:06:58.710 align:middle line:84%
And that I would
never learn any more

00:06:58.710 --> 00:07:01.420 align:middle line:84%
than what you'd
teach a chimpanzee.

00:07:01.420 --> 00:07:05.650 align:middle line:84%
Well, my older
brother-- when you

00:07:05.650 --> 00:07:08.690 align:middle line:84%
have a family that has a
member of the family like me,

00:07:08.690 --> 00:07:11.590 align:middle line:84%
essentially the whole family
becomes dysfunctional.

00:07:11.590 --> 00:07:13.830 align:middle line:84%
And it was especially
bad for my older brother

00:07:13.830 --> 00:07:16.740 align:middle line:84%
because he was the one that
had to take care of me.

00:07:16.740 --> 00:07:19.940 align:middle line:84%
So he harbored a great deal
is animosity towards me,

00:07:19.940 --> 00:07:22.910 align:middle line:84%
and I can understand why
he did a lot of the things

00:07:22.910 --> 00:07:24.190 align:middle line:90%
that he did now.

00:07:24.190 --> 00:07:26.290 align:middle line:84%
Of course, back then
I didn't understand.

00:07:26.290 --> 00:07:28.920 align:middle line:90%
But he would tease me.

00:07:28.920 --> 00:07:30.560 align:middle line:84%
One of the ways
he would tease me

00:07:30.560 --> 00:07:33.950 align:middle line:84%
is see he would say
that I was supposed

00:07:33.950 --> 00:07:38.160 align:middle line:84%
to be a monkey in a jungle, but
I wound up being his brother

00:07:38.160 --> 00:07:39.640 align:middle line:90%
instead.

00:07:39.640 --> 00:07:41.670 align:middle line:84%
And the thing that
really got to me

00:07:41.670 --> 00:07:44.760 align:middle line:84%
was he would say I was
a mistake God made,

00:07:44.760 --> 00:07:48.440 align:middle line:84%
and that my older brother
was being tortured by that.

00:07:48.440 --> 00:07:56.010 align:middle line:84%
And I didn't have sophisticated
enough thought ability to know

00:07:56.010 --> 00:07:59.290 align:middle line:84%
that I was being teased, or I
wasn;t being told the truth.

00:07:59.290 --> 00:08:02.620 align:middle line:84%
So literally, during most
of that period of time

00:08:02.620 --> 00:08:06.620 align:middle line:84%
after I began having the
ability to understand,

00:08:06.620 --> 00:08:11.360 align:middle line:84%
my conception was that I was a
mistake, I was an abomination,

00:08:11.360 --> 00:08:14.280 align:middle line:84%
I was something that
shouldn't exist.

00:08:14.280 --> 00:08:16.870 align:middle line:90%
But I did exist.

00:08:16.870 --> 00:08:21.670 align:middle line:84%
And it wasn't until
much later than that,

00:08:21.670 --> 00:08:27.890 align:middle line:84%
when I was 17 years old,
I actually had an IQ test.

00:08:27.890 --> 00:08:30.910 align:middle line:84%
And at that point,
they stopped calling me

00:08:30.910 --> 00:08:33.600 align:middle line:84%
idiot, imbecile,
and words like that.

00:08:33.600 --> 00:08:35.539 align:middle line:90%
>>What did you test out to?

00:08:35.539 --> 00:08:40.940 align:middle line:84%
>>The first testing we did
I scored 137 points on an IQ

00:08:40.940 --> 00:08:41.844 align:middle line:90%
tests.

00:08:41.844 --> 00:08:43.510 align:middle line:84%
And they said, oh my,
we made a mistake.

00:08:43.510 --> 00:08:45.850 align:middle line:90%
He's got a IQ.

00:08:45.850 --> 00:08:47.760 align:middle line:90%
>>Big mistake.

00:08:47.760 --> 00:08:49.330 align:middle line:84%
>>And at that
point, the decision

00:08:49.330 --> 00:08:51.080 align:middle line:84%
was made that I would
get speech therapy

00:08:51.080 --> 00:08:53.650 align:middle line:84%
and I would learn how
to talk in sentences.

00:08:53.650 --> 00:08:58.730 align:middle line:84%
And they also wanted educate me,
so they were going to teach me

00:08:58.730 --> 00:09:00.200 align:middle line:84%
how to read, and
write, and spell,

00:09:00.200 --> 00:09:02.050 align:middle line:90%
and all of the normal things

00:09:02.050 --> 00:09:03.298 align:middle line:90%
>>Beginning at age 17.

00:09:03.298 --> 00:09:04.130 align:middle line:90%
>>Yeah.

00:09:04.130 --> 00:09:05.780 align:middle line:90%
And the speech therapy worked.

00:09:05.780 --> 00:09:07.350 align:middle line:90%
It was absolutely wonderful.

00:09:07.350 --> 00:09:09.685 align:middle line:84%
I had a fantastic
speech therapist.

00:09:09.685 --> 00:09:12.530 align:middle line:84%
Her name was Doctor
Meredith Evans.

00:09:12.530 --> 00:09:15.440 align:middle line:84%
And I wish she could have
lived to the point where

00:09:15.440 --> 00:09:17.550 align:middle line:84%
she could see what
I'm doing today.

00:09:17.550 --> 00:09:20.450 align:middle line:90%
She would be impressed, I think.

00:09:20.450 --> 00:09:25.880 align:middle line:84%
And if you're at all
aware of our organization,

00:09:25.880 --> 00:09:27.630 align:middle line:84%
there's a great deal
of her influence

00:09:27.630 --> 00:09:31.120 align:middle line:90%
and the essence of who she is.

00:09:31.120 --> 00:09:34.010 align:middle line:84%
Her spirit very
much is a reflection

00:09:34.010 --> 00:09:36.320 align:middle line:90%
of many of the things we do.

00:09:36.320 --> 00:09:41.110 align:middle line:84%
Without her I would
still be hiding

00:09:41.110 --> 00:09:43.690 align:middle line:84%
in the back of the closet
behind the clothes.

00:09:43.690 --> 00:09:47.378 align:middle line:84%
>>But with her help, you were
able to make magnificent leaps

00:09:47.378 --> 00:09:50.030 align:middle line:90%
between the ages of 17 and 19.

00:09:50.030 --> 00:09:55.620 align:middle line:84%
>>Well, actually, the speech
therapy, in the beginning,

00:09:55.620 --> 00:09:59.130 align:middle line:84%
was a very painful thing
for me to experience.

00:09:59.130 --> 00:10:01.880 align:middle line:84%
In fact, I ran
away from it twice.

00:10:01.880 --> 00:10:06.460 align:middle line:84%
And the third time, when I came
back, she told me the truth.

00:10:06.460 --> 00:10:09.400 align:middle line:84%
She told me that she
wasn't able to fix me.

00:10:09.400 --> 00:10:12.090 align:middle line:84%
The only person that
could do that was myself.

00:10:12.090 --> 00:10:15.110 align:middle line:84%
Now, she was willing
to help me get there.

00:10:15.110 --> 00:10:17.110 align:middle line:84%
But if I was going
to make it, I was

00:10:17.110 --> 00:10:19.460 align:middle line:84%
going to have to
do it by myself.

00:10:19.460 --> 00:10:24.110 align:middle line:84%
And that little
piece of information

00:10:24.110 --> 00:10:28.040 align:middle line:90%
is what made all work actually.

00:10:28.040 --> 00:10:32.250 align:middle line:84%
And then I got involved
in the reading training.

00:10:32.250 --> 00:10:34.990 align:middle line:84%
And a lot of people
would think that there's

00:10:34.990 --> 00:10:38.270 align:middle line:84%
been a great deal of improvement
over the years in the way

00:10:38.270 --> 00:10:41.260 align:middle line:84%
they were treating
dyslexic individuals,

00:10:41.260 --> 00:10:43.710 align:middle line:84%
but to tell you
the truth, not so.

00:10:43.710 --> 00:10:45.880 align:middle line:84%
So one of the things
I had to do is

00:10:45.880 --> 00:10:49.700 align:middle line:84%
I had to crawl around on the
floor for an hour every day.

00:10:49.700 --> 00:10:51.570 align:middle line:84%
I had to balance
on a teeter board

00:10:51.570 --> 00:10:55.770 align:middle line:84%
and on a balance board for
a little while every day.

00:10:55.770 --> 00:10:59.450 align:middle line:84%
And then I was subjected
to a great deal of phonics.

00:10:59.450 --> 00:11:04.470 align:middle line:84%
I have to tell you that I was
pretty good at crawling around.

00:11:04.470 --> 00:11:05.700 align:middle line:90%
That was easy.

00:11:05.700 --> 00:11:09.020 align:middle line:84%
I was also very
good at the balance.

00:11:09.020 --> 00:11:11.800 align:middle line:84%
But the phonics for me
was absolute torture.

00:11:11.800 --> 00:11:15.520 align:middle line:84%
Within the first five minutes
of every one of those sessions

00:11:15.520 --> 00:11:20.110 align:middle line:84%
it would literally become
emotional and physical pain

00:11:20.110 --> 00:11:22.250 align:middle line:90%
for me to try to endure it.

00:11:22.250 --> 00:11:27.280 align:middle line:84%
And after almost a year of
being subjected to that,

00:11:27.280 --> 00:11:28.530 align:middle line:90%
everybody gave up.

00:11:28.530 --> 00:11:30.880 align:middle line:84%
Now I had given up
long before that,

00:11:30.880 --> 00:11:32.420 align:middle line:90%
but then everybody else did.

00:11:32.420 --> 00:11:34.680 align:middle line:84%
And the medical doctor
that was on the staff

00:11:34.680 --> 00:11:37.490 align:middle line:84%
there told me that I
was never ever going

00:11:37.490 --> 00:11:39.040 align:middle line:90%
to learn how to read and write.

00:11:39.040 --> 00:11:40.680 align:middle line:84%
And the reason
for it was, when I

00:11:40.680 --> 00:11:43.530 align:middle line:84%
was being born the
doctor used instruments,

00:11:43.530 --> 00:11:46.010 align:middle line:84%
he pinched my head, and he
ruined that part of my brain

00:11:46.010 --> 00:11:48.772 align:middle line:84%
that I would need to use
to learn how to read.

00:11:48.772 --> 00:11:52.120 align:middle line:84%
>>They didn't know much
about dyslexia at this time?

00:11:52.120 --> 00:11:54.160 align:middle line:90%
>>Well, they still don't.

00:11:54.160 --> 00:11:57.171 align:middle line:84%
When I told my mom
what the doctor said,

00:11:57.171 --> 00:11:58.670 align:middle line:84%
my mom said, no,
that didn't happen.

00:11:58.670 --> 00:12:01.360 align:middle line:84%
She said that my
birth happened so fast

00:12:01.360 --> 00:12:03.500 align:middle line:84%
there wasn't time
for instruments.

00:12:03.500 --> 00:12:08.590 align:middle line:84%
But also my mom didn't
always tell me the truth.

00:12:08.590 --> 00:12:11.090 align:middle line:84%
But it did make my
life a little easier.

00:12:11.090 --> 00:12:12.840 align:middle line:84%
It was easier at
that point for me

00:12:12.840 --> 00:12:14.560 align:middle line:84%
to believe that it
was a mistake that

00:12:14.560 --> 00:12:17.900 align:middle line:84%
was made by a doctor, a
man, and not a mistake

00:12:17.900 --> 00:12:19.340 align:middle line:90%
that God had made.

00:12:19.340 --> 00:12:24.660 align:middle line:84%
And that I was or I had
justification for existing.

00:12:24.660 --> 00:12:27.770 align:middle line:90%


00:12:27.770 --> 00:12:31.572 align:middle line:84%
Now in spite of all this,
I became an engineer.

00:12:31.572 --> 00:12:33.155 align:middle line:84%
Even though I couldn't
read and write.

00:12:33.155 --> 00:12:34.260 align:middle line:90%
>>Were you self taught?

00:12:34.260 --> 00:12:36.035 align:middle line:84%
>>Everything for me
