were you were having some real
gratification in the workforce

00:21:42.640 --> 00:21:45.620 align:middle line:84%
to beginning your
understanding with working

00:21:45.620 --> 00:21:47.380 align:middle line:90%
with a dyslexic mind?

00:21:47.380 --> 00:21:50.960 align:middle line:84%
>>There were a lot of different
condentations between then

00:21:50.960 --> 00:21:53.640 align:middle line:90%
and now.

00:21:53.640 --> 00:21:56.950 align:middle line:84%
When I stopped being a hippy,
I started to Volkswagen repair

00:21:56.950 --> 00:21:58.435 align:middle line:90%
shop in San Francisco.

00:21:58.435 --> 00:22:02.210 align:middle line:84%
I mean, that's not a bad thing
for an ex-engineer to do.

00:22:02.210 --> 00:22:09.436 align:middle line:84%
Not long after that, I created
a metals brokerage company.

00:22:09.436 --> 00:22:13.080 align:middle line:84%
And not long after that,
I started my career

00:22:13.080 --> 00:22:14.910 align:middle line:90%
in real estate.

00:22:14.910 --> 00:22:16.790 align:middle line:84%
And not long after
that, I realized

00:22:16.790 --> 00:22:19.770 align:middle line:84%
the great American dream for
the second time in my life,

00:22:19.770 --> 00:22:22.390 align:middle line:84%
and that was to
be a millionaire.

00:22:22.390 --> 00:22:30.520 align:middle line:84%
And in the late 1960s,
the real estate market

00:22:30.520 --> 00:22:35.770 align:middle line:84%
started to slow down and
my wife and I retired.

00:22:35.770 --> 00:22:40.380 align:middle line:90%


00:22:40.380 --> 00:22:42.680 align:middle line:90%
Excuse me, I misstated.

00:22:42.680 --> 00:22:45.630 align:middle line:84%
In the late 1970s,
the real estate market

00:22:45.630 --> 00:22:48.210 align:middle line:84%
started to slow down, my
wife and I retired out

00:22:48.210 --> 00:22:49.500 align:middle line:90%
of real estate.

00:22:49.500 --> 00:22:53.510 align:middle line:84%
And we had more
than enough money

00:22:53.510 --> 00:22:57.740 align:middle line:84%
for the rest of our lives, no
matter what we wanted to do.

00:22:57.740 --> 00:23:04.150 align:middle line:84%
So I was 36 years old
and I was retired.

00:23:04.150 --> 00:23:07.510 align:middle line:84%
Now, one of the
things I did is I

00:23:07.510 --> 00:23:14.640 align:middle line:84%
hid my shame behind
being successful.

00:23:14.640 --> 00:23:21.100 align:middle line:84%
In other words, I was hiding
my low self esteem behind work.

00:23:21.100 --> 00:23:24.952 align:middle line:84%
And when you're hiding
the fact that you're

00:23:24.952 --> 00:23:29.080 align:middle line:84%
a mistake that God made, or
a mistake that some man made,

00:23:29.080 --> 00:23:33.170 align:middle line:84%
and that you're not a real human
being, what better way to hid

00:23:33.170 --> 00:23:36.840 align:middle line:90%
it then behind being successful.

00:23:36.840 --> 00:23:38.580 align:middle line:90%
Excuse me.

00:23:38.580 --> 00:23:41.990 align:middle line:90%
So I was being successful.

00:23:41.990 --> 00:23:44.760 align:middle line:84%
And in order to
do that, I didn't

00:23:44.760 --> 00:23:46.670 align:middle line:90%
work like a normal human being.

00:23:46.670 --> 00:23:49.630 align:middle line:84%
I worked between 12
and 20 hours every day,

00:23:49.630 --> 00:23:52.000 align:middle line:90%
and I did work every day.

00:23:52.000 --> 00:23:55.300 align:middle line:84%
So I never went to
the movies, I worked.

00:23:55.300 --> 00:23:57.980 align:middle line:84%
I never went to church,
never went to weddings

00:23:57.980 --> 00:24:00.360 align:middle line:84%
or funerals because
I was working.

00:24:00.360 --> 00:24:03.530 align:middle line:84%
I never want to parties, I
never went to the theater

00:24:03.530 --> 00:24:05.170 align:middle line:90%
because I worked.

00:24:05.170 --> 00:24:06.570 align:middle line:84%
And I was very
successful at work

00:24:06.570 --> 00:24:10.220 align:middle line:84%
because no one ever discovered
that I couldn't read.

00:24:10.220 --> 00:24:11.330 align:middle line:90%
>>During all of that--

00:24:11.330 --> 00:24:12.580 align:middle line:90%
>>During all of that.

00:24:12.580 --> 00:24:14.150 align:middle line:90%
>>Absolutely amazing.

00:24:14.150 --> 00:24:17.210 align:middle line:84%
>>But then we
looked at retiring,

00:24:17.210 --> 00:24:20.400 align:middle line:84%
and retirement means
that you don't work.

00:24:20.400 --> 00:24:23.750 align:middle line:84%
And the idea of retiring
wasn't a bad idea.

00:24:23.750 --> 00:24:27.390 align:middle line:84%
But what was a bad
idea was not working,

00:24:27.390 --> 00:24:29.460 align:middle line:84%
because I lost my
ability to hide.

00:24:29.460 --> 00:24:34.390 align:middle line:84%
Now, it isn't just that I
was hiding my inadequacy

00:24:34.390 --> 00:24:38.280 align:middle line:84%
from other people, I was
also hiding it from myself.

00:24:38.280 --> 00:24:40.070 align:middle line:84%
And what was happening
is, with every day,

00:24:40.070 --> 00:24:41.653 align:middle line:84%
I was getting more
and more depressed.

00:24:41.653 --> 00:24:44.530 align:middle line:84%
Of course, I didn't realize
that's what it was at the time.

00:24:44.530 --> 00:24:48.280 align:middle line:84%
And I'm not the kind of person
that will go to a doctor.

00:24:48.280 --> 00:24:51.350 align:middle line:84%
I'm afraid of them, I
just don't like them.

00:24:51.350 --> 00:24:54.010 align:middle line:84%
>>They didn't serve you well
in childhood, it sounds like.

00:24:54.010 --> 00:24:59.630 align:middle line:84%
>>Well, I'm not going to
get very deep into that,

00:24:59.630 --> 00:25:01.510 align:middle line:84%
because I could
get into trouble.

00:25:01.510 --> 00:25:05.224 align:middle line:84%
But I came to a point
where I realized

00:25:05.224 --> 00:25:06.890 align:middle line:84%
that I was going to
have to do something

00:25:06.890 --> 00:25:11.430 align:middle line:84%
about the way I was feeling
or I was going to die.

00:25:11.430 --> 00:25:17.370 align:middle line:84%
And for me, all of my life art
has been the real narcotic.

00:25:17.370 --> 00:25:19.680 align:middle line:84%
If I get involved
with something--

00:25:19.680 --> 00:25:21.980 align:middle line:84%
even if it's simply drawing
something, or sketching

00:25:21.980 --> 00:25:24.070 align:middle line:84%
something, or chipping
a piece of stone,

00:25:24.070 --> 00:25:27.380 align:middle line:84%
or carving a piece of wood, or
making something out of clay,

00:25:27.380 --> 00:25:30.020 align:middle line:84%
or painting-- literally,
the rest of world

00:25:30.020 --> 00:25:33.090 align:middle line:84%
goes away until I finished
doing what I was doing.

00:25:33.090 --> 00:25:38.420 align:middle line:84%
And I felt that if I couldn't
hide my problem behind work,

00:25:38.420 --> 00:25:41.870 align:middle line:84%
I could be oblivious
to it with art.

00:25:41.870 --> 00:25:43.750 align:middle line:84%
Now, I didn't feel that
I had enough talent

00:25:43.750 --> 00:25:46.810 align:middle line:84%
to earn a living as an artist,
but I was in a position

00:25:46.810 --> 00:25:50.890 align:middle line:84%
that I needed to earn a living,
so I started to play with it.

00:25:50.890 --> 00:25:53.922 align:middle line:84%
And within a year, I was
working as a portrait sculptor

00:25:53.922 --> 00:25:56.130 align:middle line:84%
and I discovered that I
could make a wonderful living

00:25:56.130 --> 00:25:57.730 align:middle line:90%
as an artist.

00:25:57.730 --> 00:26:00.500 align:middle line:84%
To the point that, if I ever
have the misfortune again

00:26:00.500 --> 00:26:04.530 align:middle line:84%
of retiring, I'm going to go
back and be an artist again.

00:26:04.530 --> 00:26:07.910 align:middle line:84%
Because for me, it was like
dying and doing to heaven.

00:26:07.910 --> 00:26:10.540 align:middle line:84%
And it was when I was
working as an artist I began

00:26:10.540 --> 00:26:12.580 align:middle line:84%
to notice things that
didn't make sense

00:26:12.580 --> 00:26:14.670 align:middle line:90%
to the engineering in me.

00:26:14.670 --> 00:26:18.380 align:middle line:84%
What I noticed was that when
I was at my artistic best,

00:26:18.380 --> 00:26:21.240 align:middle line:90%
I was at my dyslexic worst.

00:26:21.240 --> 00:26:23.880 align:middle line:84%
And I had believed
that my problem

00:26:23.880 --> 00:26:25.420 align:middle line:90%
was a structural problem.

00:26:25.420 --> 00:26:28.350 align:middle line:84%
I believed the reason I couldn't
learn how to read and write

00:26:28.350 --> 00:26:30.690 align:middle line:84%
was because I had
brain damage, which

00:26:30.690 --> 00:26:32.510 align:middle line:84%
means it is a
structural problem.

00:26:32.510 --> 00:26:36.120 align:middle line:84%
And one of the things
about a structural problem

00:26:36.120 --> 00:26:38.810 align:middle line:84%
is that the characteristics
of the problem

00:26:38.810 --> 00:26:41.540 align:middle line:90%
has to remain the same.

00:26:41.540 --> 00:26:44.400 align:middle line:84%
And I was noticing that it
wasn't remaining the same.

00:26:44.400 --> 00:26:46.710 align:middle line:84%
And my thinking
was, I can't have

00:26:46.710 --> 00:26:48.930 align:middle line:84%
brain damage this afternoon
and tomorrow morning it's

00:26:48.930 --> 00:26:50.430 align:middle line:84%
going to go away
for a little while,

00:26:50.430 --> 00:26:52.920 align:middle line:84%
tomorrow afternoon it's
going to come back again.

00:26:52.920 --> 00:26:55.900 align:middle line:90%
That cannot work.

00:26:55.900 --> 00:26:58.630 align:middle line:84%
Then the thinking was,
well, if the problem is not

00:26:58.630 --> 00:27:01.621 align:middle line:84%
a structural problem,
then what can it be?

00:27:01.621 --> 00:27:03.870 align:middle line:84%
And the answer is, the only
other thing that it can be

00:27:03.870 --> 00:27:06.260 align:middle line:84%
is that it's a
functional problem.

00:27:06.260 --> 00:27:08.210 align:middle line:84%
If it is a functional
problem that means

00:27:08.210 --> 00:27:11.000 align:middle line:84%
I am either doing
something that causes it,

00:27:11.000 --> 00:27:14.450 align:middle line:84%
or I'm failing to do something
and that's what causes it.

00:27:14.450 --> 00:27:16.440 align:middle line:84%
And with that thinking,
I became a researcher

00:27:16.440 --> 00:27:18.330 align:middle line:90%
in the field of dyslexia.

00:27:18.330 --> 00:27:21.210 align:middle line:84%
And within 36 hours
after starting looking,

00:27:21.210 --> 00:27:23.420 align:middle line:84%
I discovered something
that I could do inside

00:27:23.420 --> 00:27:27.020 align:middle line:84%
of my head that made all of
the symptoms simply go away.

00:27:27.020 --> 00:27:29.650 align:middle line:84%
And that day, I
went to a library

00:27:29.650 --> 00:27:31.810 align:middle line:84%
and I read a book from
cover to cover in one day.

00:27:31.810 --> 00:27:34.320 align:middle line:90%


00:27:34.320 --> 00:27:36.540 align:middle line:84%
>>Can you share in this
moment, or do we need to--

00:27:36.540 --> 00:27:37.921 align:middle line:90%
>>What book it was?

00:27:37.921 --> 00:27:38.420 align:middle line:90%
>>No.

00:27:38.420 --> 00:27:40.211 align:middle line:84%
What it was that you
could go in your hear.

00:27:40.211 --> 00:27:44.140 align:middle line:84%
I discovered what we
now call orientation.

00:27:44.140 --> 00:27:46.890 align:middle line:84%
Now, what I discovered was
a very rudimentary form.

00:27:46.890 --> 00:27:49.690 align:middle line:90%
It was just the beginning of it.

00:27:49.690 --> 00:27:52.622 align:middle line:84%
But when I was in
an oriented state,

00:27:52.622 --> 00:27:54.080 align:middle line:84%
the words on the
bottom of the page

00:27:54.080 --> 00:27:56.550 align:middle line:84%
were just as big as the
words on the top of the page.

00:27:56.550 --> 00:27:58.610 align:middle line:84%
There were spaces
between the letters,

00:27:58.610 --> 00:28:02.080 align:middle line:84%
there was actually
punctuation marks.

00:28:02.080 --> 00:28:05.110 align:middle line:84%
Literally, the letters didn't
run together with the words,

00:28:05.110 --> 00:28:06.610 align:middle line:84%
there were spaces
between the words,

00:28:06.610 --> 00:28:08.490 align:middle line:90%
you could clearly see them.

00:28:08.490 --> 00:28:10.630 align:middle line:84%
And I had been struggling
to learn how to read,

00:28:10.630 --> 00:28:13.300 align:middle line:84%
or struggling with
reading, my whole life.

00:28:13.300 --> 00:28:16.720 align:middle line:84%
Now, prior to that day it isn't
that I couldn't read at all--

00:28:16.720 --> 00:28:18.900 align:middle line:84%
I would say that what
the average person could

00:28:18.900 --> 00:28:21.700 align:middle line:84%
reading maybe five minutes,
I could get through it

00:28:21.700 --> 00:28:25.230 align:middle line:84%
in maybe an hour, maybe
a little more than that.

00:28:25.230 --> 00:28:27.890 align:middle line:84%
But I would never be really
certain if I got it all

00:28:27.890 --> 00:28:30.570 align:middle line:90%
or if I got it correctly.

00:28:30.570 --> 00:28:34.430 align:middle line:84%
But what I discovered was
this very rudimentary form

00:28:34.430 --> 00:28:37.040 align:middle line:90%
of orientation.

00:28:37.040 --> 00:28:39.450 align:middle line:84%
And I read a whole
book in one day.

00:28:39.450 --> 00:28:43.750 align:middle line:84%
Now, I never dreamed of the
ability to read a whole book.

00:28:43.750 --> 00:28:46.410 align:middle line:84%
For me, that dream would
have been a nightmare.

00:28:46.410 --> 00:28:49.554 align:middle line:84%
I never prayed for the
ability to read a whole book.

00:28:49.554 --> 00:28:51.220 align:middle line:84%
I didn't think that's
the kind of prayer

00:28:51.220 --> 00:28:53.030 align:middle line:90%
that God would answer.

00:28:53.030 --> 00:28:56.660 align:middle line:84%
So one day in my life,
I had an experience

00:28:56.660 --> 00:28:58.480 align:middle line:84%
that was beyond my
ability to dream

00:28:58.480 --> 00:29:00.750 align:middle line:90%
and beyond my ability to pray.

00:29:00.750 --> 00:29:02.970 align:middle line:84%
And as a result of
that experience,

00:29:02.970 --> 00:29:05.530 align:middle line:90%
two things occurred.

00:29:05.530 --> 00:29:07.260 align:middle line:84%
The most important
thing that occurred

00:29:07.260 --> 00:29:09.540 align:middle line:84%
was that it was the
first day of my life

00:29:09.540 --> 00:29:13.650 align:middle line:84%
that I considered myself
as a real human being.

00:29:13.650 --> 00:29:19.340 align:middle line:84%
I considered myself as not being
a mistake that anyone had made,

00:29:19.340 --> 00:29:22.550 align:middle line:84%
and that I had just as much
right as any other human

00:29:22.550 --> 00:29:23.705 align:middle line:90%
to be alive.

00:29:23.705 --> 00:29:28.320 align:middle line:84%
>>Now you're getting at the real
heart of the issue of dyslexia

00:29:28.320 --> 00:29:33.580 align:middle line:84%
is this sense of being less
than that each of these people

00:29:33.580 --> 00:29:34.860 align:middle line:90%
carry with them.

00:29:34.860 --> 00:29:35.573 align:middle line:90%
>>Indeed.

00:29:35.573 --> 00:29:36.400 align:middle line:90%
Indeed.

00:29:36.400 --> 00:29:39.835 align:middle line:84%
>>And so what did this
do to inspire you then

00:29:39.835 --> 00:29:43.160 align:middle line:84%
to launch into this
as a life path?

00:29:43.160 --> 00:29:44.957 align:middle line:90%
>>Several things.

00:29:44.957 --> 00:29:46.540 align:middle line:84%
The other thing that
happened that day

00:29:46.540 --> 00:29:50.770 align:middle line:84%
is, I made a mistake in thinking
that I cured myself of dyslexia

00:29:50.770 --> 00:29:53.230 align:middle line:84%
Now prior to then, I
had never told anyone

00:29:53.230 --> 00:29:54.710 align:middle line:90%
that I had dyslexia.

00:29:54.710 --> 00:29:56.350 align:middle line:84%
It is something that
I was ashamed of.

00:29:56.350 --> 00:29:58.240 align:middle line:90%
I didn't want anyone to know.

00:29:58.240 --> 00:30:01.080 align:middle line:84%
In fact, I went to great
lengths to hide it from people.

00:30:01.080 --> 00:30:02.530 align:middle line:84%
But after I thought
I was cured, I

00:30:02.530 --> 00:30:05.540 align:middle line:84%
didn't waste any time
telling people I was cured.

00:30:05.540 --> 00:30:08.952 align:middle line:84%
And surprisingly,
a lot of people

00:30:08.952 --> 00:30:10.410 align:middle line:84%
came out of the
woodwork, it seemed

00:30:10.410 --> 00:30:15.230 align:middle line:84%
like, that asked me
if I would help them.

00:30:15.230 --> 00:30:19.160 align:middle line:84%
And prior to that
point in time, I

00:30:19.160 --> 00:30:21.030 align:middle line:84%
didn't know anyone
else that had dyslexia.

00:30:21.030 --> 00:30:23.550 align:middle line:90%


00:30:23.550 --> 00:30:29.740 align:middle line:84%
Literally, I thought I was a
lot more rare than I really was.

00:30:29.740 --> 00:30:32.860 align:middle line:84%
And I didn't know any other
people that were dyslexic.

00:30:32.860 --> 00:30:34.770 align:middle line:84%
And it turns out,
there were a lot of us

00:30:34.770 --> 00:30:37.330 align:middle line:84%
that were hiding
it from each other.

00:30:37.330 --> 00:30:40.070 align:middle line:84%
And I started doing
with them the same kind

00:30:40.070 --> 00:30:42.350 align:middle line:90%
of torture I put myself through.

00:30:42.350 --> 00:30:45.450 align:middle line:84%
And literally, we started
to see tremendous change.

00:30:45.450 --> 00:30:49.380 align:middle line:84%
But I also, along
the way, realized

00:30:49.380 --> 00:30:52.780 align:middle line:84%
that I hadn't actually
cured myself of dyslexia.

00:30:52.780 --> 00:30:55.220 align:middle line:84%
I realized at the very
most all I had found

00:30:55.220 --> 00:30:57.120 align:middle line:84%
was a piece to a
puzzle, and there

00:30:57.120 --> 00:30:59.100 align:middle line:84%
were other puzzle pieces
that had to be found.

00:30:59.100 --> 00:31:01.400 align:middle line:84%
>>Was the beginning
point you're were

00:31:01.400 --> 00:31:03.690 align:middle line:84%
talking about, about
finding this orientation?

00:31:03.690 --> 00:31:05.030 align:middle line:90%
>>Yes.

00:31:05.030 --> 00:31:07.730 align:middle line:84%
And in fact, what I was
doing, I didn't even

00:31:07.730 --> 00:31:11.180 align:middle line:84%
understand at the time
that's what it was.

00:31:11.180 --> 00:31:16.740 align:middle line:84%
So this actually occurred--
the break through actually

00:31:16.740 --> 00:31:19.580 align:middle line:90%
occurred in December of 1980.

00:31:19.580 --> 00:31:23.700 align:middle line:84%
By April of 1981, I
realized I wasn't cured.

00:31:23.700 --> 00:31:28.000 align:middle line:84%
And shortly after that,
I and two other people

00:31:28.000 --> 00:31:30.910 align:middle line:84%
created the Reading
Research Council.

00:31:30.910 --> 00:31:33.410 align:middle line:84%
And we had two
basic goals in mind.

00:31:33.410 --> 00:31:35.580 align:middle line:90%
And I had a hidden agenda.

00:31:35.580 --> 00:31:38.310 align:middle line:84%
The first goal was to
see if we could find out

00:31:38.310 --> 00:31:39.522 align:middle line:90%
what dyslexia really was.

00:31:39.522 --> 00:31:41.730 align:middle line:84%
To see if we could find the
rest of the puzzle pieces

00:31:41.730 --> 00:31:43.700 align:middle line:90%
that it was composed of.

00:31:43.700 --> 00:31:46.180 align:middle line:84%
The second goal was, if
we find the puzzle pieces,

00:31:46.180 --> 00:31:49.140 align:middle line:84%
to see if we could figure out
how to put that puzzle together

00:31:49.140 --> 00:31:51.650 align:middle line:84%
so we could actually
cure dyslexia.

00:31:51.650 --> 00:31:55.485 align:middle line:84%
Of course, at that time,
we didn't understand it

00:31:55.485 --> 00:31:58.760 align:middle line:84%
to the point to realize that
we wouldn't want to cure it.

00:31:58.760 --> 00:32:01.080 align:middle line:84%
And my hidden agenda
was, I'm paying for this

00:32:01.080 --> 00:32:04.820 align:middle line:84%
so I get to be the
first person in line.

00:32:04.820 --> 00:32:09.950 align:middle line:84%
So by December of
1981, we had enough

00:32:09.950 --> 00:32:14.330 align:middle line:84%
of a rudimentary understanding
of the puzzle pieces

00:32:14.330 --> 00:32:16.520 align:middle line:84%
that we could start
to put them together.

00:32:16.520 --> 00:32:20.290 align:middle line:84%
And by April of 1982, we
knew what would actually

00:32:20.290 --> 00:32:23.950 align:middle line:84%
have to be done in
order to correct it.

00:32:23.950 --> 00:32:26.300 align:middle line:84%
We hadn't done it
yet, but we knew

00:32:26.300 --> 00:32:31.530 align:middle line:84%
what we would have to do in
order to make that happen.

00:32:31.530 --> 00:32:37.130 align:middle line:84%
And in April of 1982,
we started working

00:32:37.130 --> 00:32:40.220 align:middle line:90%
with individuals in the public.

00:32:40.220 --> 00:32:43.790 align:middle line:84%
And the first year that
we were in operation,

00:32:43.790 --> 00:32:47.160 align:middle line:90%
we had a 93% success rate.

00:32:47.160 --> 00:32:48.930 align:middle line:90%
>>Did you have them crawling?

00:32:48.930 --> 00:32:51.360 align:middle line:90%
>>No, absolutely not.

00:32:51.360 --> 00:32:54.560 align:middle line:84%
That just shows the
ignorance the people.

00:32:54.560 --> 00:32:58.430 align:middle line:84%
When we first started
looking at dyslexia,

00:32:58.430 --> 00:33:01.600 align:middle line:84%
there were two prevailing
beliefs-- actually,

00:33:01.600 --> 00:33:05.925 align:middle line:84%
there were three-- prevailing
beliefs about what dyslexia was

00:33:05.925 --> 00:33:07.420 align:middle line:90%
and what caused it.

00:33:07.420 --> 00:33:09.950 align:middle line:84%
The first one goes
clear back to 1896,

00:33:09.950 --> 00:33:13.080 align:middle line:84%
and it was the original
definition of dyslexia.

00:33:13.080 --> 00:33:15.545 align:middle line:84%
And there are some
controversy over exactly who

00:33:15.545 --> 00:33:17.290 align:middle line:90%
it is that coined the word.

00:33:17.290 --> 00:33:20.620 align:middle line:90%
I'm in the British camp.

00:33:20.620 --> 00:33:25.690 align:middle line:84%
I think the word was coined by
a physician in the Glasgow Eye

00:33:25.690 --> 00:33:27.590 align:middle line:90%
Infirmary in Scotland.

00:33:27.590 --> 00:33:29.850 align:middle line:90%
His name was James Hinshelwood.

00:33:29.850 --> 00:33:34.870 align:middle line:84%
And he defined dyslexia
as a form aphasia marked

00:33:34.870 --> 00:33:38.120 align:middle line:84%
by the inability to
develop cyphering skills,

00:33:38.120 --> 00:33:40.480 align:middle line:84%
probable location of
the aphasiac lesion

00:33:40.480 --> 00:33:42.380 align:middle line:90%
left angular gyrus.

00:33:42.380 --> 00:33:43.410 align:middle line:90%
He was a medical doctor.

00:33:43.410 --> 00:33:45.860 align:middle line:84%
He's talking so that
we can't understand.

00:33:45.860 --> 00:33:49.190 align:middle line:84%
The word "aphasia" means the
loss or the lack of the ability

00:33:49.190 --> 00:33:52.890 align:middle line:84%
to use or understand language,
caused brain damage or nerve

00:33:52.890 --> 00:33:55.440 align:middle line:84%
damage from either
illness or injury.

00:33:55.440 --> 00:33:59.050 align:middle line:90%
So it is a form of brain damage.

00:33:59.050 --> 00:34:02.170 align:middle line:84%
And then he goes on to say the
probable location of the brain

00:34:02.170 --> 00:34:06.390 align:middle line:84%
damage is the left angular
gyrus of the brain.

00:34:06.390 --> 00:34:08.889 align:middle line:84%
That, oddly enough, is
still the medical definition

00:34:08.889 --> 00:34:11.560 align:middle line:90%
of the word dyslexia.

00:34:11.560 --> 00:34:16.090 align:middle line:84%
In the early 1920s, 30s, there
was an American physician,

00:34:16.090 --> 00:34:19.590 align:middle line:84%
his name was Doctor
Samuel Torrey Orton,

00:34:19.590 --> 00:34:23.830 align:middle line:90%
who tried to redefine dyslexia.

00:34:23.830 --> 00:34:26.010 align:middle line:84%
And his first attempt
at redefining it

00:34:26.010 --> 00:34:31.510 align:middle line:84%
was, he said that dyslexia is a
product of cross lateralization

00:34:31.510 --> 00:34:32.719 align:middle line:90%
of the brain.

00:34:32.719 --> 00:34:34.969 align:middle line:84%
And what that means is that
the left side of the brain

00:34:34.969 --> 00:34:38.219 align:middle line:84%
does what the right side
should do, and vice versa.

00:34:38.219 --> 00:34:41.429 align:middle line:84%
And even though he
authored that theory,

00:34:41.429 --> 00:34:43.470 align:middle line:84%
it wasn't very long
after it was published

00:34:43.470 --> 00:34:46.400 align:middle line:90%
that he changed his mind.

00:34:46.400 --> 00:34:48.230 align:middle line:84%
But even though he
changed his mind,

00:34:48.230 --> 00:34:51.000 align:middle line:84%
there were a lot of people
that still followed it.

00:34:51.000 --> 00:34:54.150 align:middle line:84%
And he watered it
down some and said

00:34:54.150 --> 00:34:57.319 align:middle line:84%
that it was mixed
hemispheric dominance.

00:34:57.319 --> 00:34:59.360 align:middle line:84%
Meaning that sometimes
the left side of the brain

00:34:59.360 --> 00:35:02.740 align:middle line:84%
is doing what the right side
should do, and vice versa.

00:35:02.740 --> 00:35:07.115 align:middle line:84%
And that is the primary
psychological belief

00:35:07.115 --> 00:35:09.340 align:middle line:90%
of what dyslexia is.

00:35:09.340 --> 00:35:14.980 align:middle line:84%
So both of these go back to
either our brains are miswired,

00:35:14.980 --> 00:35:17.490 align:middle line:84%
or there's actual
brain damage that

00:35:17.490 --> 00:35:20.320 align:middle line:84%
is there that is preventing
something from occurring.

00:35:20.320 --> 00:35:22.770 align:middle line:84%
And what we found
out is that, even

00:35:22.770 --> 00:35:26.280 align:middle line:84%
though both of these theories
sound good, sound reasonable,

00:35:26.280 --> 00:35:28.050 align:middle line:90%
they're incorrect.

00:35:28.050 --> 00:35:30.900 align:middle line:84%
Dyslexia is actually a
product of three things.

00:35:30.900 --> 00:35:34.950 align:middle line:84%
It is a product of thought,
it as a product of talent,

00:35:34.950 --> 00:35:39.010 align:middle line:84%
and it is product
of a low tolerance

00:35:39.010 --> 00:35:43.550 align:middle line:84%
or a low threshold
for confusion.

00:35:43.550 --> 00:35:48.600 align:middle line:84%
So when we started
working with dyslexia,

00:35:48.600 --> 00:35:51.510 align:middle line:84%
we thought we were
looking for a cure.

00:35:51.510 --> 00:35:55.590 align:middle line:84%
Well, if you consider
that a part of dyslexia

00:35:55.590 --> 00:35:59.760 align:middle line:84%
comes from talent, the only
cure for a talent that I know of

00:35:59.760 --> 00:36:01.170 align:middle line:90%
is death.

00:36:01.170 --> 00:36:05.060 align:middle line:84%
So I don't think we really
want to have a cure for it.

00:36:05.060 --> 00:36:07.290 align:middle line:84%
So we will settle
for the next best

00:36:07.290 --> 00:36:10.700 align:middle line:84%
thing, which is a
correction for it.

00:36:10.700 --> 00:36:17.460 align:middle line:84%
And the basic philosophy
behind everything that I do

00:36:17.460 --> 00:36:21.210 align:middle line:84%
is that, if you eliminate the
reason why a problem exists,

00:36:21.210 --> 00:36:28.000 align:middle line:84%
the problem will stop
existing or causing someone

00:36:28.000 --> 00:36:29.450 align:middle line:90%
to be oriented.

00:36:29.450 --> 00:36:31.900 align:middle line:84%
All of the symptoms
of dyslexia are

00:36:31.900 --> 00:36:35.590 align:middle line:84%
symptoms of the
disorientated state.

00:36:35.590 --> 00:36:38.750 align:middle line:84%
If the person to simply
turn off being disoriented,

00:36:38.750 --> 00:36:40.650 align:middle line:90%
they can turn off the symptoms.

00:36:40.650 --> 00:36:45.790 align:middle line:84%
And that's what I was doing
that I mistook for a cure.

00:36:45.790 --> 00:36:48.620 align:middle line:84%
When I realized that I wasn't
cured, that all I had done

00:36:48.620 --> 00:36:50.980 align:middle line:84%
was found a piece
to a puzzle, we

00:36:50.980 --> 00:36:54.120 align:middle line:84%
had to then dig a little
bit deeper into the puzzle

00:36:54.120 --> 00:36:56.680 align:middle line:84%
and find out what it
is that was actually

00:36:56.680 --> 00:36:59.490 align:middle line:84%
causing it to be there
in the first place.

00:36:59.490 --> 00:37:03.430 align:middle line:84%
And we discovered that it was
the feeling of confusion that

00:37:03.430 --> 00:37:06.730 align:middle line:84%
was stimulating
the disorientation.

00:37:06.730 --> 00:37:11.230 align:middle line:84%
So we isolated where the
sources of that confusion were.

00:37:11.230 --> 00:37:14.460 align:middle line:84%
And by mastering the
sources of the confusion,

00:37:14.460 --> 00:37:18.520 align:middle line:84%
we're eliminating the reason
why the problem exists

00:37:18.520 --> 00:37:19.860 align:middle line:90%
as a problem.

00:37:19.860 --> 00:37:22.290 align:middle line:84%
Now, we're not
curing the dyslexia.

00:37:22.290 --> 00:37:26.720 align:middle line:84%
We're not causing people who are
primarily thinking with images

00:37:26.720 --> 00:37:29.960 align:middle line:84%
to suddenly think
with sounds of words.

00:37:29.960 --> 00:37:31.940 align:middle line:84%
They may or may not
ever develop that skill

00:37:31.940 --> 00:37:33.830 align:middle line:90%
and it doesn't matter.

00:37:33.830 --> 00:37:38.440 align:middle line:84%
I think most people to
think primarily with images

00:37:38.440 --> 00:37:41.300 align:middle line:84%
or feel that they're
very much slowed down

00:37:41.300 --> 00:37:44.420 align:middle line:84%
by this cumbersome
slow word thinking

00:37:44.420 --> 00:37:46.600 align:middle line:84%
process-- the other
kind of thinking

00:37:46.600 --> 00:37:48.605 align:middle line:84%
is so much faster and
so much more accurate.

00:37:48.605 --> 00:37:51.670 align:middle line:90%


00:37:51.670 --> 00:37:56.900 align:middle line:84%
>>From that point,
you ended up even

00:37:56.900 --> 00:37:59.280 align:middle line:84%
expressing dyslexia
as a gift and writing

00:37:59.280 --> 00:38:01.540 align:middle line:84%
a book called "The
Gift of Dyslexia".

00:38:01.540 --> 00:38:03.652 align:middle line:84%
Now, can you talk
about this as a gift?

00:38:03.652 --> 00:38:05.610 align:middle line:84%
And then I want to go
back to this point you're

00:38:05.610 --> 00:38:07.900 align:middle line:84%
talking about, about the
brain having to slow down

00:38:07.900 --> 00:38:12.080 align:middle line:84%
to assimilate information
in black and white digits.

00:38:12.080 --> 00:38:16.230 align:middle line:84%
>>Well, we can read a
lot faster than-- it

00:38:16.230 --> 00:38:17.940 align:middle line:90%
doesn't have to go slow.

00:38:17.940 --> 00:38:20.520 align:middle line:84%
As long as you
understand the mechanics

00:38:20.520 --> 00:38:23.790 align:middle line:84%
of what it is it that
you're wanting to do.

00:38:23.790 --> 00:38:28.320 align:middle line:84%
The verbal communication
cannot be speeded up.

00:38:28.320 --> 00:38:30.160 align:middle line:84%
An awful lot of
dyslexic children

00:38:30.160 --> 00:38:33.040 align:middle line:84%
will have difficulty
with learning how to talk

00:38:33.040 --> 00:38:35.350 align:middle line:84%
and their speech
patterns sometimes

00:38:35.350 --> 00:38:37.270 align:middle line:90%
might even be a bit garbled.

00:38:37.270 --> 00:38:40.130 align:middle line:84%
Those things are corrected
along with correcting

00:38:40.130 --> 00:38:43.970 align:middle line:84%
the other problems that
are related to dyslexia.

00:38:43.970 --> 00:38:47.020 align:middle line:84%
Most people think that
dyslexia is a reading problem.

00:38:47.020 --> 00:38:47.640 align:middle line:90%
No.

00:38:47.640 --> 00:38:51.280 align:middle line:84%
Dyslexia affects, or can affect,
reading, writing, speaking,

00:38:51.280 --> 00:38:56.410 align:middle line:84%
spelling, mathematics,
physical coordination, and also

00:38:56.410 --> 00:38:59.876 align:middle line:90%
our perception of time.

00:38:59.876 --> 00:39:01.334 align:middle line:84%
>>Dyslexia then
doesn't necessarily

00:39:01.334 --> 00:39:04.490 align:middle line:84%
mean that a person simply
has a reading disability?

00:39:04.490 --> 00:39:07.450 align:middle line:84%
>>Well the word
dyslexia, we use it

00:39:07.450 --> 00:39:10.790 align:middle line:90%
because it is the parent term.

00:39:10.790 --> 00:39:14.080 align:middle line:84%
The different aspects
of dyslexia-- and there

00:39:14.080 --> 00:39:17.290 align:middle line:84%
are more than 80 different
words that they use now

00:39:17.290 --> 00:39:19.600 align:middle line:84%
for different
aspects of dyslexia.

00:39:19.600 --> 00:39:21.270 align:middle line:84%
And the current,
most popular one,

00:39:21.270 --> 00:39:24.970 align:middle line:90%
is attention deficit disorder.

00:39:24.970 --> 00:39:28.860 align:middle line:84%
We consider it just another
one of the aspects of dyslexia.

00:39:28.860 --> 00:39:32.590 align:middle line:84%
And all of it is correctable,
we can correct every form of it.

00:39:32.590 --> 00:39:37.140 align:middle line:84%
>>Let's go to the next higher
octave, how is this a gift?

00:39:37.140 --> 00:39:39.870 align:middle line:84%
>>In evaluating
how a person would

00:39:39.870 --> 00:39:43.530 align:middle line:84%
go about developing
dyslexia, there

00:39:43.530 --> 00:39:45.770 align:middle line:84%
are certain characteristics
that we have.

00:39:45.770 --> 00:39:51.760 align:middle line:84%
And the first one is, we are
born with the genetic code that

00:39:51.760 --> 00:39:55.200 align:middle line:84%
allows us to do things that
a normal person would not

00:39:55.200 --> 00:39:57.850 align:middle line:90%
be able to do.

00:39:57.850 --> 00:39:59.980 align:middle line:84%
And what it allows
us to do is, it

00:39:59.980 --> 00:40:04.240 align:middle line:84%
allows us to cause a
disorientation to occur.

00:40:04.240 --> 00:40:06.420 align:middle line:90%
Now, all human beings disorient.

00:40:06.420 --> 00:40:09.330 align:middle line:90%
It is a normal, natural thing.

00:40:09.330 --> 00:40:11.950 align:middle line:84%
In fact, this
disorientation is one

00:40:11.950 --> 00:40:14.990 align:middle line:84%
of the things you have to do in
order to go to sleep at night.

00:40:14.990 --> 00:40:17.240 align:middle line:84%
If you ever have a sudden
feeling like you're falling,

00:40:17.240 --> 00:40:20.720 align:middle line:84%
or your body suddenly jerks
just before you go to sleep,

00:40:20.720 --> 00:40:24.010 align:middle line:84%
that's the moment when
the disorientation occurs.

00:40:24.010 --> 00:40:25.590 align:middle line:84%
If you've ever
had the experience

00:40:25.590 --> 00:40:28.970 align:middle line:84%
of riding in a vehicle or
sitting in a vehicle that's

00:40:28.970 --> 00:40:30.780 align:middle line:84%
stationary, something
outside the vehicle

00:40:30.780 --> 00:40:33.510 align:middle line:84%
moves and you have the
sensation that you're moving,

00:40:33.510 --> 00:40:35.910 align:middle line:84%
that fall sensation, or
that false perception,

00:40:35.910 --> 00:40:37.970 align:middle line:90%
is coming from disorientation.

00:40:37.970 --> 00:40:39.660 align:middle line:90%
It happens to everyone.

00:40:39.660 --> 00:40:42.410 align:middle line:84%
But some of us are born
with the genetic code that

00:40:42.410 --> 00:40:47.430 align:middle line:84%
allows us to do it without
an outside stimuli.

00:40:47.430 --> 00:40:51.740 align:middle line:84%
And we discover this
ability very early in life,

00:40:51.740 --> 00:40:55.090 align:middle line:84%
probably before
we're six months old.

00:40:55.090 --> 00:40:59.730 align:middle line:84%
We discover that by using
that part of our anatomy,

00:40:59.730 --> 00:41:03.020 align:middle line:84%
we can actually perceive things
that other people wouldn't

00:41:03.020 --> 00:41:04.220 align:middle line:90%
be able to perceive.

00:41:04.220 --> 00:41:06.770 align:middle line:84%
We can hear maybe
10 times better

00:41:06.770 --> 00:41:08.200 align:middle line:90%
than a normal human being.

00:41:08.200 --> 00:41:13.210 align:middle line:84%
Our ability to detect smells
and odors can be much enhanced.

00:41:13.210 --> 00:41:16.440 align:middle line:84%
Literally, is like being able
to see around corners or see

00:41:16.440 --> 00:41:18.710 align:middle line:90%
through walls.

00:41:18.710 --> 00:41:21.650 align:middle line:84%
So probably the very
first time any of us

00:41:21.650 --> 00:41:24.130 align:middle line:84%
ever use our ability
to disorient,

00:41:24.130 --> 00:41:27.570 align:middle line:84%
we use it to recognize our
mother, the person that

00:41:27.570 --> 00:41:30.070 align:middle line:90%
feeds us.

00:41:30.070 --> 00:41:33.660 align:middle line:84%
And we then expand
the use of that

00:41:33.660 --> 00:41:35.540 align:middle line:84%
to other things in
the environment.

00:41:35.540 --> 00:41:38.660 align:middle line:84%
And as a result of that, we
will become very environmentally

00:41:38.660 --> 00:41:39.980 align:middle line:90%
aware.

00:41:39.980 --> 00:41:43.490 align:middle line:84%
Much more so than a
normal human being.

00:41:43.490 --> 00:41:47.260 align:middle line:84%
And we can explore the
environment mentally much more

00:41:47.260 --> 00:41:52.880 align:middle line:84%
thoroughly than a normal human
being would be able to do.

00:41:52.880 --> 00:41:57.960 align:middle line:84%
But in doing this, we also
create a crossroads for us.

00:41:57.960 --> 00:42:00.130 align:middle line:84%
Our early childhood
development isn't

00:42:00.130 --> 00:42:03.000 align:middle line:84%
going to go straight down the
way it does for other children.

00:42:03.000 --> 00:42:05.940 align:middle line:84%
You look at the early
childhood development books

00:42:05.940 --> 00:42:10.060 align:middle line:84%
that most expectant
mothers will look at,

00:42:10.060 --> 00:42:12.710 align:middle line:84%
and they read about what they
can expect from their child.

00:42:12.710 --> 00:42:14.080 align:middle line:90%
We're not going to do that.

00:42:14.080 --> 00:42:16.780 align:middle line:90%


00:42:16.780 --> 00:42:20.300 align:middle line:90%
Let's take just one of these.

00:42:20.300 --> 00:42:27.100 align:middle line:84%
An individual who is exploring
the environment mentally

00:42:27.100 --> 00:42:30.910 align:middle line:84%
will either be very
motivated to become mobile.

00:42:30.910 --> 00:42:33.760 align:middle line:84%
In other words, they're very
motivated now to get out

00:42:33.760 --> 00:42:36.059 align:middle line:84%
there and not just
explore it mentally,

00:42:36.059 --> 00:42:38.350 align:middle line:84%
but to get their hands on
it, to get it in their mouth,

00:42:38.350 --> 00:42:40.400 align:middle line:90%
to explore it physically.

00:42:40.400 --> 00:42:42.310 align:middle line:84%
So a person like
this is going to be

00:42:42.310 --> 00:42:46.470 align:middle line:84%
very motivated to
control movement.

00:42:46.470 --> 00:42:49.734 align:middle line:84%
So they will start crawling very
early, and by the time they're

00:42:49.734 --> 00:42:51.650 align:middle line:84%
supposed to start crawling,
they're already up

00:42:51.650 --> 00:42:53.490 align:middle line:90%
and running around.

00:42:53.490 --> 00:42:57.567 align:middle line:84%
But on the other hand, the
person has already explored it.

00:42:57.567 --> 00:42:59.150 align:middle line:84%
They already know
where it is and what

00:42:59.150 --> 00:43:01.830 align:middle line:84%
it is, they don't
need to be mobile.

00:43:01.830 --> 00:43:04.360 align:middle line:84%
So they aren't motivated
to become mobile.

00:43:04.360 --> 00:43:08.030 align:middle line:84%
So the time to start crawling
comes and goes, they don't.

00:43:08.030 --> 00:43:10.030 align:middle line:84%
It's time for them
to start walking,

00:43:10.030 --> 00:43:12.880 align:middle line:84%
and they're still not
even crawling very well.

00:43:12.880 --> 00:43:15.760 align:middle line:84%
And everyone thinks that there's
something wrong with the child.

00:43:15.760 --> 00:43:20.620 align:middle line:84%
The only thing that's wrong
is they're not motivated.

00:43:20.620 --> 00:43:23.780 align:middle line:84%
The same thing happens
with talking and language.

00:43:23.780 --> 00:43:27.420 align:middle line:84%
On one route, you can be very
motivated to communicate.

00:43:27.420 --> 00:43:31.300 align:middle line:84%
On the other route, you have
no need to communicate at all.

00:43:31.300 --> 00:43:35.340 align:middle line:84%
So if you go down the route
where it happens quickly,

00:43:35.340 --> 00:43:37.330 align:middle line:84%
everybody thinks
that you're advanced.

00:43:37.330 --> 00:43:37.830 align:middle line:90%
Right?

